				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Have the teachings and ministries at Mile Hi Church made an impact on you? For many of us, Mile Hi Church has changed our lives for the better. Consider playing a part in preserving the programs that the Foundation supports to ensure these teachings live on in perpetuity.</p>
<p>As our annual <a href="https://quantumcreativecommunications.com/dev/project/foundation-february/">Foundation February</a> event kicks off, be sure to stop by Foundation booths before and after Sunday services during the month of February. Foundation Directors and Ambassadors will be on hand to greet you with a cheery smile, a gift, and to answer any questions you might have about the Foundation or membership.</p>
<h3>Dinner With a Minister</h3>
<p>You won&#8217;t want to miss this! Stop by and visit one of the Foundation booths, either in the west Sanctuary lobby or in the Community Center, and you can register for our dinner with a minister drawing!</p>
<p>The Foundation will provide a $200 gift certificate to a local restaurant where you and your plus one can dine with Dr. Michelle or Rev. Joshua. What a great opportunity to spend time with these beautiful souls (and ask any burning questions)!</p>
<h3>Estate Planning Workshop for Non-Traditional Families</h3>
<p>As we all well know, one of the treasured aspects of attending Mile Hi Church is its welcoming embrace of all people. In today&#8217;s world, the typical mom, dad and children family scenarios now share space with blended families, marriages later in life, children of divorced parents, grandparents raising grandchildren, common law marriages, same sex, and other types of families.</p>
<p>On Saturday, February 17, the Foundation is hosting attorney Bridget McCann from 9:30 &#8211; 11:30 AM in the chapel. She will be presenting advice on estate planning for non-traditional families. Don&#8217;t miss this important workshop!</p>
<p>We look forward to seeing you during Foundation February</p>
